                        <item>
                           <note xml:lang="en">Avraham E. Harkavy (1835–1919) was appointed to the department of Jewish literature and oriental manuscripts at the Imperial Public Library of St. Petersburg in 1868. In 1876, he was made head of the Department of Hebrew Books, and in 1877 appointed as ordinary librarian, a position which he held for the rest of his life. He was the first curator of the Firkovitch collections. His unpublished cataloging of these collections consists of slips of paper ("Harkavy cards"), placed together with each manuscript, that record his identification of and/or a brief description of that manuscript. These slips were the foundation for his handwritten four-volume inventory of the Yevr.-Arab. section of the Second Firkovitch Collection. </note>
